Parameters
Variables can be passed as a parameter

Special parameters
$# is the number of arguments passed
$0 is the name of the script
$2 is the second argument passed
$* is ALL the arguments passed
$? Is the exit status of the last command ran
$_ is the lsat argument of the previous command
$$ is the PID of the current shell
$- is the flags that are set
Functions

The goal of a function is to break your code up into manageable reusable blocks

function start() {			
echo "Does this function work?"	
}					
					
Start					


	
function getuserchoice() {		
    	echo "Make a choice [1,2,3]:"	
    	read userchoice		
    	case $userchoice in		
            	(1) echo one ;;		
            	(2) echo two ;;		
            	(3) echo three ;;	
            	(*) echo other ;;	
    	Esac				
}					

Getuserchoice				
	







function folder() {		
    	if [ ! -s $1 ]; then	
            	mkdir $1	
    	Else			
            	echo "STOP"	
            	return 1	
    	fi }			

folder $1			

Variable Substitution in Functions:


function sub1 () {							
    	name="Joe"							
    	echo $name                  	#Joe				
}									
function sub2 () {							
    	name="Joe"							
    	echo "My name is $name"     	#My name is Joe		
}									
function sub3 () {							
    	name="Joe"							
    	echo 'My name is $name'     	#My name is $name		
}									
function sub4 () {							
    	name="Joe"							
    	echo "My name is $nameny5"  	#My name is		
    	echo "My name is ${name}n5" 	#My name is Joen5	
}									
function sub5 () {							
    	name="Joe"							
    	echo ${name:0:2}            	#Jo				
}			
